0
00:00:35,768 --> 00:00:37,963
[Crowd chattering, cheering]

1
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:51,477
[Crowd] Hannah! Hannah! Hannah!

2
00:00:59,625 --> 00:01:01,422
[Chattering, cheering continues]

3
00:01:19,512 --> 00:01:21,707
What is with all the pushing behind me?

4
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:22,942
Here you go, girls.

5
00:01:23,649 --> 00:01:25,913
It's Miley Stewart.
We've got to get in there.

6
00:01:25,952 --> 00:01:27,681
Our names are on the list.

7
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:32,157
Well, why didn't you say so?
In your dreams, sweet cheeks. Next!

8
00:01:32,191 --> 00:01:34,751
- No, no. They're on there. I promise.
- We need two.

9
00:01:36,429 --> 00:01:39,592
You are the only pop star I know
who can't get into her own concert.

10
00:01:39,632 --> 00:01:43,227
She was just here.
I don't know where she went.

11
00:01:47,373 --> 00:01:49,238
- [Man] Stop!
- [Lilly] Go!

12
00:01:49,275 --> 00:01:51,140
[Yelling]

13
00:01:51,177 --> 00:01:53,008
Somebody, stop those girls!

14
00:01:53,045 --> 00:01:55,912
- Go faster!
- I can't! This is a golf cart!

15
00:01:55,948 --> 00:01:57,916
Stop!

16
00:01:57,950 --> 00:02:00,919
Those girls shouldn't be here!
They don't have a backstage pass!

17
00:02:00,953 --> 00:02:04,354
- What are you doing?
- [Man] Stop in the name of Security!

18
00:02:04,390 --> 00:02:05,857
- Watch out!
- [Man] I need backup!

19
00:02:05,892 --> 00:02:09,419
Call for backup! Whoa!

20
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:11,453
- Yes!
- Yes! Oh!

21
00:02:11,497 --> 00:02:13,055
[Both screaming]

22
00:02:19,906 --> 00:02:21,703
[Both laughing]

23
00:02:23,342 --> 00:02:25,037
Stop!

24
00:02:25,077 --> 00:02:28,877
- Please stop!
- It's OK. It's OK. They're with me.

25
00:02:28,915 --> 00:02:31,281
Come on. Go, go, go.

26
00:02:52,271 --> 00:02:53,898
Hey.

27
00:02:57,276 --> 00:02:58,504
Dad.

28
00:02:59,212 --> 00:03:00,236
What?

29
00:03:28,841 --> 00:03:30,536
[Exhales]

30
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:34,904
- Showtime, baby doll.
- [Sputters]

31
00:03:36,215 --> 00:03:38,342
- She's on the move.
- [Man] All right, let's go.

32
00:03:38,384 --> 00:03:40,716
Good luck! Don't mess up!

33
00:03:42,655 --> 00:03:44,555
This way. Follow me.

34
00:03:51,664 --> 00:03:53,529
- Come on.
- She's coming right now.

35
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:54,897
[Man] All right, talent's on its way.

36
00:03:54,934 --> 00:03:57,425
- Oh!
- You do that every night.

37
00:03:59,572 --> 00:04:02,063
- Love you, Daddy.
- I'm loving you right back, darling.

38
00:04:02,108 --> 00:04:04,736
Don't forget it's your turn
to do the dishes tonight.

39
00:04:04,777 --> 00:04:05,937
I did them last night.

40
00:04:05,978 --> 00:04:09,436
Don't give me no lip. You're the one
that wanted the best of both worlds.

41
00:04:09,482 --> 00:04:11,712
[<i>#</i> Hannah Montana: <i>The Best Of</i>
<i>Both Worlds: The 2009 Movie Mix]</i>

42
00:04:11,751 --> 00:04:14,982
- [Crowd] Hannah! Hannah! Hannah!
- Watch your head.

43
00:04:16,188 --> 00:04:19,521
Here we go, everybody! Whoo!

44
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:26,298
Oh, yeah.

45
00:04:26,332 --> 00:04:27,856
Come on.

46
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:49,170
[Hawaiian music playing]

47
00:06:12,938 --> 00:06:15,236
Cut! We'll fix that last bit in post.

48
00:06:15,274 --> 00:06:17,299
- That's a wrap, people.
- [All cheering]

49
00:06:17,343 --> 00:06:20,244
- Hannah, as always, fabulous.
- Thank you.

50
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:23,248
[Indistinct chattering]

51
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:38,830
No. It's OK. I'm sorry.
I just had to meet you.

52
00:06:38,864 --> 00:06:41,355
I promised my girls
I'd say hi to you for them.

53
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,890
- Hi.
- Hi.

54
00:06:42,935 --> 00:06:46,063
They even wrote out some
questions, if you have a second.

55
00:06:46,105 --> 00:06:50,371
Oh, my gosh, this is
such a thrill. Do you mind?

56
00:06:50,409 --> 00:06:53,071
- Not at all.
- Don't even think about it.

57
00:06:53,112 --> 00:06:55,672
- No, Vita. It's OK.
- Nothing about this man is OK.

58
00:06:55,715 --> 00:06:57,774
Hello, Oswald.

59
00:06:57,817 --> 00:07:00,115
Hello, Vita. Looking lovely as ever.

60
00:07:00,152 --> 00:07:03,644
Icky teeth, really?
Isn't that beneath even you?

61
00:07:03,689 --> 00:07:07,853
Oswald Granger, chief sleaze
of <i>Bon Chic</i> magazine,

62
00:07:07,893 --> 00:07:09,793
Britain's most notorious tabloid.

63
00:07:09,829 --> 00:07:12,389
And we would love, with a capital "ove,"

64
00:07:12,431 --> 00:07:15,992
to do a cover feature on the global
phenomenon that is Hannah Montana.

65
00:07:16,035 --> 00:07:18,765
And by "feature" he means
"career-ending expose."

66
00:07:18,804 --> 00:07:22,296
"Country girl living her dreams beloved
by millions," that's all we got.

67
00:07:22,341 --> 00:07:24,332
That's all you're gonna get.
Now get out.

68
00:07:25,811 --> 00:07:27,938
[Oswald] Can't blame a bloke for trying.

69
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:31,848
How could you even think
we have something to hide?

70
00:07:31,884 --> 00:07:34,546
- He didn't see anything, did he?
- I don't think so.

71
00:07:34,587 --> 00:07:36,054
[Vita] Good. Hannah, honey,

72
00:07:36,155 --> 00:07:38,487
you can't talk to anyone
unless I'm at your side.

73
00:07:38,524 --> 00:07:41,550
I'm your publicist. You need to
concentrate on what you do best

74
00:07:41,594 --> 00:07:43,926
which is singing
your scrappy little heart out.

75
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:45,828
Let me worry about everything else,

76
00:07:45,865 --> 00:07:49,926
like making sure your
little secret stays a secret.

77
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:52,369
Sometimes I wish I could
be Hannah all the time.

78
00:07:52,404 --> 00:07:54,269
You and me both, kid.

79
00:07:54,306 --> 00:07:57,742
Out of the way, you jackals.
Step aside. Coming through.

80
00:07:57,777 --> 00:08:00,371
That's right, don't touch the pop star.
Move aside.

81
00:08:09,855 --> 00:08:14,451
<i>[Vita]... like making sure</i>
<i>your litle secret stays a secret.</i>

82
00:08:14,493 --> 00:08:17,724
Secret? What secret?
Move your bum, you old cow.

83
00:08:17,763 --> 00:08:20,391
[Phone ringing]

84
00:08:21,634 --> 00:08:25,126
Talk to me, Ozzie,
and don't disappoint.

85
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:29,335
- Apparently there's a secret.
- Good. Because the cover's ready.

86
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:31,570
I just need the story to go with it.

87
00:08:31,610 --> 00:08:36,206
Find out that secret. She's the most
popular teenager in the world.

88
00:08:36,248 --> 00:08:39,411
<i>So I suggest you go out</i>
<i>and find me every juicy,</i>

89
00:08:39,451 --> 00:08:44,150
sordid detail of Hannah Montana's
outrageous, glamorous life.

90
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:48,424
- [Grunts]
- [Applause]

91
00:08:48,460 --> 00:08:51,520
All right. Line it up, people.
We're going to choose new teams.

92
00:08:51,564 --> 00:08:55,364
Dead girl in the middle
of the floor. Anybody?

93
00:08:57,570 --> 00:08:59,868
Fabulous news:
Beyonce has double pneumonia.

94
00:08:59,905 --> 00:09:02,533
Has to drop out of the
New York Music Awards. You're in!

95
00:09:02,575 --> 00:09:04,133
That is great. Not for Beyonce.

96
00:09:04,176 --> 00:09:06,440
I really should call.
But, yes! I'm so excited!

97
00:09:06,478 --> 00:09:08,537
What am I gonna sing?
What am I gonna wear?

98
00:09:08,581 --> 00:09:11,311
Great minds. The car and the box
are already outside,

99
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:13,409
so Hannah has to do a major shop now.

100
00:09:13,452 --> 00:09:15,852
Last chance. Come on.

101
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:19,016
Miley? Hello?
What about my birthday party?

102
00:09:19,058 --> 00:09:21,959
Minor Hannah emergency.
I'll be there, I promise.

103
00:09:25,931 --> 00:09:27,523
[Vita] Wasn't that fun?

104
00:09:27,566 --> 00:09:30,433
Yeah, but it feels weird having
them give me stuff for free.

105
00:09:30,469 --> 00:09:34,735
Please. Do you know what a well-placed
photo of you shopping is worth?

106
00:09:34,773 --> 00:09:36,570
You're a star, an icon.

107
00:09:36,609 --> 00:09:39,942
You look at it, touch it, wear it,
and the whole world has to have it.

108
00:09:39,979 --> 00:09:43,107
They owe it to you, Hannah.
Name it and it's yours.

109
00:09:43,148 --> 00:09:45,708
- Really?
- I have so much to teach you.

110
00:09:48,287 --> 00:09:50,653
If she doesn't hurry,
you're going to miss your plane.

111
00:09:50,689 --> 00:09:56,594
Yeah, that's right, losers! I'm going
to college! Tennessee Universi...

112
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:59,291
- University.
- Where is that girl?

113
00:10:00,199 --> 00:10:02,861
[Japanese music playing]

114
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:05,598
- I can't decide.
- Decide? No deciding. Too stressful.

115
00:10:05,638 --> 00:10:08,266
Take them all. We'll just
add them to the pile. Girls.

116
00:10:08,307 --> 00:10:10,104
- [Snaps]
- Ooh.

117
00:10:10,142 --> 00:10:12,667
Watches. I totally need a new watch.

118
00:10:12,711 --> 00:10:14,702
Is that the time? I can't believe it.

119
00:10:14,747 --> 00:10:18,513
We got to go.
Eleven messages. Jackson.

120
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:21,542
Lilly's present. Lilly...
would totally love those shoes.

121
00:10:25,224 --> 00:10:27,920
- She will so love these.
- I'm sorry. I saw these first.

122
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,154
Can you wrap these for me?

123
00:10:29,194 --> 00:10:31,355
They're for my best friend.
She's 16 today.

124
00:10:31,397 --> 00:10:33,331
Funny, they're for my best friend, too.

125
00:10:33,365 --> 00:10:34,627
My best friend is a six and a half.

126
00:10:34,667 --> 00:10:36,999
Funny, my best friend's
a six and a half, too.

127
00:10:37,036 --> 00:10:40,563
Tyra Banks, that's our only pair.

128
00:10:40,606 --> 00:10:44,269
- Not funny. Do you know who I am?
- I know you know who I am.

129
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:45,334
- So?
- So?

130
00:10:45,377 --> 00:10:46,469
- So?
- So?

131
00:10:46,512 --> 00:10:50,642
- Give me that shoe.
- Get away from me!

132
00:10:50,683 --> 00:10:55,347
You know what? If you want it, jump
for it. Jump for the shoe, Hannah.

133
00:10:55,387 --> 00:10:56,854
Fine. Gimme!

134
00:10:57,589 --> 00:10:58,920
[Grunts] Got it!

135
00:10:59,725 --> 00:11:02,888
[Both shouting]

136
00:11:02,928 --> 00:11:05,795
[<i>#</i> Hannah Montana: <i>The Good Life</i>]

137
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:07,765
[Both grunting]

138
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,791
Yes! Yes!

139
00:11:12,638 --> 00:11:14,196
Give me my shoe, lady!

140
00:11:22,514 --> 00:11:23,845
She is so in trouble.

141
00:11:27,753 --> 00:11:31,211
No, you didn't! Hannah Montana!

142
00:11:33,592 --> 00:11:36,789
- Yes!
- [Tyra] I appreciate you helping me up,

143
00:11:36,829 --> 00:11:39,354
but I don't appreciate
you not helping me with this.

144
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:46,364
[All clamoring]

145
00:11:46,405 --> 00:11:48,839
Relax? Are you kidding me?
Have you met my dad?

146
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:52,241
He is not gonna shake off me missing
saying goodbye to Jackson.

147
00:11:52,277 --> 00:11:53,904
[Man] Give us a smile. You look amazing.

148
00:11:53,946 --> 00:11:55,277
Thank you. We got to go.

149
00:11:56,548 --> 00:11:58,516
- [Tires squealing]
- [Honking]

150
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:01,348
Hey!

151
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:05,221
And I didn't even get the shoes.
I am the worst friend in the world.

152
00:12:07,526 --> 00:12:08,925
It's him.

153
00:12:10,262 --> 00:12:12,457
Oswald. Step on it!

154
00:12:15,968 --> 00:12:17,663
I cannot get out of the car
looking like Miley,

155
00:12:17,703 --> 00:12:20,001
and I cannot show up at Lilly's
party looking like Hannah.

156
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:32,581
Where are you headed?

157
00:12:32,618 --> 00:12:34,609
[<i>#</i> Steve Rushton: <i>Game Over]</i>

158
00:12:44,663 --> 00:12:47,063
Hi! Thank you. Thank you.

159
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:50,557
[Ringtone sounding]

160
00:12:50,602 --> 00:12:53,036
Hey, Lilly. What's up?

161
00:12:53,072 --> 00:12:56,303
We've talked about this party
since we were, like, 12. Where...

162
00:12:56,341 --> 00:12:59,242
- Hi! How are you? Where are you?
- I'm almost there.

163
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:01,371
- [Sighs]
- She hung up on...

164
00:13:01,413 --> 00:13:04,439
- [ringtone sounds]
- Where are you? Everybody's waiting...

165
00:13:04,483 --> 00:13:06,348
- Sorry, wrong number!
- Miley!

166
00:13:06,385 --> 00:13:09,377
Two smoothies, please.
Where's Miley? We haven't seen her.

167
00:13:09,421 --> 00:13:11,685
Just spoke with her.
She'll be here any second.

168
00:13:11,723 --> 00:13:14,248
[<i>#</i> Steve Rushton: <i>Everything I Want]</i>

169
00:13:16,595 --> 00:13:18,756
Rico, what's this hole
at the top of the cake?

170
00:13:20,332 --> 00:13:23,165
It's a high-pressure
electro-pneumatic solenoid on it.

171
00:13:23,202 --> 00:13:27,662
It's 150 pounds per square inch
with a brass safety-check valve.

172
00:13:27,706 --> 00:13:31,938
Then I just hit this button
and bam! Sparklers go off,

173
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:35,572
and a "happy birthday, Lilly" banner
shoots out the top of the cake.

174
00:13:35,614 --> 00:13:38,447
Once again...
[rolling R] Rico is a genius.

175
00:13:50,129 --> 00:13:54,589
Hold it! This is a private event.
Guests only! What did I tell you? Stop!

176
00:13:54,633 --> 00:13:56,066
- Smile.
- No pictures.

177
00:14:00,572 --> 00:14:04,064
[Gasps] That's what I call a Lilly...
Wow.

178
00:14:04,109 --> 00:14:05,906
[Girl] It's Hannah Montana!

179
00:14:05,944 --> 00:14:09,038
- [All screaming]
- Is that Hannah Montana?

180
00:14:09,081 --> 00:14:10,378
- [Screams]
- [Thuds]

181
00:14:11,383 --> 00:14:15,012
[Groaning]

182
00:14:23,962 --> 00:14:25,725
Guys, I'm only here... Wait!

183
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:30,798
Happy birthday to... I want to say happy
birthday to my number one fan, Lilly.

184
00:14:30,836 --> 00:14:33,930
She's over that way.
She's over that way.

185
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:40,042
Happy birthday, Lilly. Happy birthday.

186
00:14:40,612 --> 00:14:43,604
I'm sorry. I had no choice.
I'll make it up to you, I promise.

187
00:14:43,649 --> 00:14:47,551
You will never, ever, ever
make it up to me.

188
00:14:48,620 --> 00:14:51,646
- I'm sorry.
- [Helicopter whirring]

189
00:14:54,660 --> 00:14:57,720
[Crowd] Sing, sing, sing, sing, sing.

190
00:14:57,763 --> 00:15:00,197
[Chanting continues]

191
00:15:04,803 --> 00:15:08,534
<i>Crazy, Crazy,</i>
<i>Crazy, Crazy, Crazy.</i>

192
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:11,202
Uh, you guys know the words
to <i>Let's Get Crazy?</i>

193
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:14,576
[All cheering]

194
00:15:19,218 --> 00:15:21,584
All right, then, here we go!

195
00:15:21,620 --> 00:15:25,750
[<i>#</i> Hannah Montana: <i>Let's Get Crazy]</i>

196
00:15:27,259 --> 00:15:30,251
[Hannah] You ready? Here we go.

197
00:15:31,863 --> 00:15:35,629
<i># Life is just a party</i>
<i>so come as you are</i>

198
00:15:35,667 --> 00:15:39,694
<i># Dress it up or dress it down</i>
<i>Don't forget your guitar, yeah</i>

199
00:15:39,738 --> 00:15:43,299
<i># Just be courageous</i>
<i>'Cause style's contagious</i>

200
00:15:43,342 --> 00:15:46,505
<i># Everyone can rock out like a superstar</i>

201
00:15:46,545 --> 00:15:50,413
<i># Let's get crazy</i>
<i>Get up and dance</i>

202
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:54,215
<i># Take a swing, do your thing</i>
<i>It's worth taking a chance</i>

203
00:15:54,253 --> 00:15:56,244
<i># Let's get crazy</i>

204
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:58,188
<i># Yeah, just kick up your heels</i>

205
00:15:58,223 --> 00:16:00,191
<i># Don't miss out</i>
<i>Time to shout</i>

206
00:16:00,225 --> 00:16:04,457
<i># Always keeping it real</i>
<i>Let's get crazy</i>

207
00:16:04,496 --> 00:16:06,589
<i># Crazy</i>

208
00:16:11,436 --> 00:16:14,564
Lilly! Lilly, we got cake!

209
00:16:14,606 --> 00:16:17,769
Hold up. Wait. Birthday Girl,
I have some questions.

210
00:16:17,809 --> 00:16:21,472
Is it true Hannah's really 43 years old?
She lip syncs? Grew up in Nashville?

211
00:16:21,513 --> 00:16:24,448
More like a cornfield in
some place called Crowley Corners.

212
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:26,508
Really? How do you spell "Crowley"?

213
00:16:26,551 --> 00:16:29,577
It's Lilly Truscott, everybody!
Happy birthday.

214
00:16:29,621 --> 00:16:31,111
We got cake over there.

215
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:33,724
Just like it sounds.

216
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:37,119
- Lilly!
- Oliver? Quick!

217
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:40,222
Light the cake. We're gonna
stop Lilly from leaving.

218
00:16:40,265 --> 00:16:43,200
Cake? No, I'm not ready yet!

219
00:16:43,235 --> 00:16:44,600
Come on! We have cake!

220
00:16:47,005 --> 00:16:50,065
[All screaming]

221
00:16:50,108 --> 00:16:53,407
- [Laughing]
- [Girl] Eww!

222
00:16:58,617 --> 00:16:59,549
[Mouthing] Sorry.

223
00:17:03,822 --> 00:17:05,687
Lilly, please pick up.

224
00:17:10,896 --> 00:17:13,922
- [Robby Ray] Did you see this?
- Yeah, I know. It's everywhere.

225
00:17:13,965 --> 00:17:16,525
Isn't it... horrible. Bad Hannah.

226
00:17:16,568 --> 00:17:18,695
She and I need to have
a little conversation.

227
00:17:18,737 --> 00:17:22,070
Now? But she's getting ready
to go to New York.

228
00:17:22,107 --> 00:17:24,735
Didn't she tell you?
There's an amazing opportunity.

229
00:17:24,776 --> 00:17:28,234
