CCed in an e-mail. Not happening.

230
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:31,477
She and I are flying to Tennessee
for her Grandma Ruby's birthday.

231
00:17:31,516 --> 00:17:33,575
Didn't she tell you?

232
00:17:33,618 --> 00:17:37,748
A shoe fight! You got
into a stinking shoe fight?

233
00:17:37,789 --> 00:17:40,121
In my defense,
I totally saw those shoes first.

234
00:17:40,158 --> 00:17:45,357
This is absolutely, T-totally,
without a doubt unacceptable.

235
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:48,264
Which pretty much describes
all of your behavior lately.

236
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:51,667
Standing up your brother?
Humiliating Lilly at her own party?

237
00:17:51,703 --> 00:17:54,763
I know. I screwed up. I'm sorry,
but I can't talk about this now.

238
00:17:54,806 --> 00:17:56,774
I got to go to New York.
It's the music awards.

239
00:17:56,808 --> 00:17:59,072
Your grandmother's birthday
doesn't matter?

240
00:17:59,111 --> 00:18:01,136
This is totally different
and you know it.

241
00:18:01,179 --> 00:18:03,443
Now, Robby. Mr. Ray.

242
00:18:03,482 --> 00:18:07,077
Father Montana, Hannah not going
to New York is really not an option.

243
00:18:07,119 --> 00:18:10,714
- Her name is Miley.
- Miley'll be back before she leaves.

244
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:13,589
She's a superstar. I can get her
a private jet if she wants.

245
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:16,219
Yes! I've always wanted
one of those.

246
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:17,660
For gosh sakes.

247
00:18:21,566 --> 00:18:24,126
Fine. You win.

248
00:18:24,169 --> 00:18:26,569
But you heard our superstar.
She needs a jet.

249
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:28,436
- Really?
- I like your thinking.

250
00:18:28,473 --> 00:18:30,100
It will take some time to arrange,

251
00:18:30,142 --> 00:18:32,872
but I'll go ahead to New York
and set up the meet and greet.

252
00:18:42,821 --> 00:18:47,417
Ooh. Next time, you might want to
demand a jet with a bigger bathroom.

253
00:18:47,459 --> 00:18:49,552
Why in the heck you
getting all Hannahed up?

254
00:18:49,594 --> 00:18:51,755
The Hannah steps off the plane photo op.

255
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:55,324
The balloons, the limos,
the screaming fans.

256
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:58,803
Like Vita says,
"It's all about the publicity."

257
00:18:58,837 --> 00:19:02,739
Yeah. That Vita's
just full of good advice.

258
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:06,406
Absolutely full of it.

259
00:19:09,581 --> 00:19:11,811
Hello, New York!

260
00:19:12,617 --> 00:19:15,211
[Cow mooing]

261
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:21,224
Looks like your limo's here.

262
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,599
Ain't she a beaut?

263
00:19:29,634 --> 00:19:32,228
Yee doggies. Tennessee.

264
00:19:38,143 --> 00:19:39,576
Dad, come on.

265
00:19:39,611 --> 00:19:42,307
Yeah, maybe I should've
remembered Grandma's birthday.

266
00:19:42,347 --> 00:19:45,077
- I did.
- Jackson, not now.

267
00:19:45,116 --> 00:19:48,677
Dad! Please, Hannah Montana
needs to be walking down the red carpet

268
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,654
in New York in less than three hours.

269
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:53,852
Miley, all you ever
wanted to do was sing.

270
00:19:53,892 --> 00:19:56,588
Hannah let you do that
and still have a normal life.

271
00:19:56,628 --> 00:19:58,391
That was the dream, remember?

272
00:19:59,798 --> 00:20:02,961
That's why we
created her in the first place.

273
00:20:03,001 --> 00:20:05,231
I don't know what she's about anymore.

274
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:08,364
- What are you saying?
- I think we might be done.

275
00:20:11,109 --> 00:20:14,840
- You can't take Hannah away from me.
- Really? Because that's what I'm doing.

276
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:18,008
No! Stop the truck. I'm not
doing this. I want to go home.

277
00:20:18,583 --> 00:20:19,777
Stop the truck!

278
00:20:38,537 --> 00:20:41,597
You are home. Look around you.

279
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:43,232
Hannah means everything to me.

280
00:20:43,275 --> 00:20:45,334
That right there might be the problem.

281
00:20:49,648 --> 00:20:51,741
You're saying I can
never be Hannah again?

282
00:20:51,783 --> 00:20:54,411
Ask me again in two weeks.

283
00:20:54,452 --> 00:20:56,818
Right now let's see
if a country girl still exists.

284
00:20:56,855 --> 00:21:00,154
- Two weeks?
- Think of it as a Hannah detox.

285
00:21:00,191 --> 00:21:02,284
Take that wig off
and get back in the truck.

286
00:21:02,327 --> 00:21:07,128
No. I'm not getting
back in the truck. No way.

287
00:21:15,574 --> 00:21:17,633
I'm not getting back in the truck, Dad.

288
00:21:17,676 --> 00:21:21,373
I'm going to New York whether you
like it or not, and I'm not... Whoa!

289
00:21:22,647 --> 00:21:24,410
Give that back, you mangy little...

290
00:21:24,449 --> 00:21:28,317
Look at that. Girl don't even
recognize her own horse.

291
00:21:28,353 --> 00:21:30,150
Now that truly is sad.

292
00:21:31,256 --> 00:21:32,553
Blue Jeans?

293
00:21:37,996 --> 00:21:41,295
Meet us at the house.
Just about a mile up the road.

294
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:51,772
Don't forget your suitcase.

295
00:21:58,617 --> 00:22:00,414
In my defense, you do look different.

296
00:22:02,387 --> 00:22:04,048
Did you do something to your tail?

297
00:22:31,349 --> 00:22:32,907
[Grunts]

298
00:22:32,951 --> 00:22:36,182
Good boy.
All right, now. Help me out.

299
00:22:37,656 --> 00:22:39,021
Hold still.

300
00:22:40,592 --> 00:22:42,651
- [Whinnies]
- [Grunts]

301
00:22:42,694 --> 00:22:44,321
Blue Jeans!

302
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,622
Blue Jeans!

303
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:51,031
[Horse galloping]

304
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:04,572
[Boy] Ya!

305
00:23:34,746 --> 00:23:36,043
[Horse snorting]

306
00:23:40,885 --> 00:23:43,012
Hi. You all right?

307
00:23:43,822 --> 00:23:46,290
Blue Jeans doesn't really
take well to strangers.

308
00:23:46,324 --> 00:23:49,623
Especially not dirty, sparkly ones.

309
00:23:51,029 --> 00:23:53,657
I know. He's my horse.

310
00:23:56,835 --> 00:23:58,097
Miley?

311
00:23:59,304 --> 00:24:01,704
It's me. Travis?

312
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:05,733
Travis Brody? We were
in the first grade together.

313
00:24:05,777 --> 00:24:08,041
Me and you went to your
Uncle Earl's farm and swam

314
00:24:08,079 --> 00:24:11,139
- and got poison oak all over our...
- I remember you, OK?

315
00:24:12,150 --> 00:24:14,710
I also remember you hanging me
headfirst down a well.

316
00:24:14,753 --> 00:24:17,881
Yeah. I guess I had a
pretty big crush on you back then.

317
00:24:17,922 --> 00:24:19,981
But don't worry about it.

318
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:24,694
I'm over it. [scoffs]

319
00:24:25,764 --> 00:24:26,992
Good to know.

320
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:31,996
Don't come around
too often anymore, do you?

321
00:24:32,036 --> 00:24:33,799
[Miley] Often enough.

322
00:24:33,838 --> 00:24:36,773
Only a couple times since your
ma died that I've heard about.

323
00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:39,333
[Clears throat]
So how long are you staying?

324
00:24:39,377 --> 00:24:40,674
- Two weeks.
- Ha!

325
00:24:40,712 --> 00:24:43,704
- Good luck with that.
- What's that supposed to mean?

326
00:24:43,748 --> 00:24:46,342
Considering what you're wearing

327
00:24:46,384 --> 00:24:48,978
and the fact that you couldn't
get back on your horse,

328
00:24:49,020 --> 00:24:50,988
I'm guessing you
went California on us.

329
00:24:51,022 --> 00:24:55,083
I have not. You don't know
anything about me or California.

330
00:24:55,894 --> 00:24:58,988
Let me guess, celebrities are
just regular folk like you and me.

331
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:01,760
- Some are.
- Oh. Uh-huh.

332
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,927
You, uh... you
actually know any?

333
00:25:04,736 --> 00:25:06,101
I know Hannah Montana.

334
00:25:07,705 --> 00:25:09,070
Hannah Montana? Really?

335
00:25:09,774 --> 00:25:12,242
Yeah. I...

336
00:25:12,277 --> 00:25:14,905
I practically saved her life
surfing the other day.

337
00:25:14,946 --> 00:25:19,440
She owes me big time. We're like...
We're like best friends.

338
00:25:20,084 --> 00:25:23,952
Huh. Best friends.

339
00:25:24,756 --> 00:25:26,917
[Grunts]

340
00:25:26,958 --> 00:25:30,485
They're all waiting for you inside.
I'll take Blue Jeans, put him away.

341
00:25:30,528 --> 00:25:34,055
- You don't have to do that.
- It's kind of my job.

342
00:25:35,266 --> 00:25:37,734
I've been working for
your grandma for the summer.

343
00:25:37,769 --> 00:25:39,259
Ooh.

344
00:25:41,906 --> 00:25:44,932
This is usually about the time
someone would say "thank you."

345
00:25:44,976 --> 00:25:47,911
- I was getting there.
- No need.

346
00:25:49,147 --> 00:25:52,378
See you round, Smiley Miley.

347
00:25:52,417 --> 00:25:55,818
Remember? That's what he used
to call you. Smiley Miley.

348
00:25:56,588 --> 00:25:59,113
- [Makes clicking sound]
- I remember.

349
00:25:59,157 --> 00:26:02,957
[<i># Backwards</i>]

350
00:26:39,430 --> 00:26:41,159
I got my Miley back!

351
00:26:44,235 --> 00:26:46,100
Come on, Miley,
take the next verse.

352
00:26:46,137 --> 00:26:49,129
- [All shouting in agreement]
- Come on.

353
00:26:52,644 --> 00:26:55,477
Get your dog back and your house back...

354
00:27:00,051 --> 00:27:02,815
I want my life back, Dad.

355
00:27:02,854 --> 00:27:06,654
- [Music stops]
- [All chattering]

356
00:27:06,691 --> 00:27:09,592
Sorry. Sorry, everybody. Hey.

357
00:27:09,627 --> 00:27:11,026
Happy birthday, Grandma.

358
00:27:11,062 --> 00:27:15,965
Well, I just blew out my candles,
and I already got my birthday wish.

359
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,764
Come here, sweet thing. Ohhh.

360
00:27:18,803 --> 00:27:22,330
I have missed you
more than you can imagine.

361
00:27:22,373 --> 00:27:24,500
And thank you.

362
00:27:24,542 --> 00:27:29,206
Thank you so much for this.
I just love it.

363
00:27:29,247 --> 00:27:31,374
There's only one King,

364
00:27:31,416 --> 00:27:36,149
and I have been saving him
a place of honor.

365
00:27:38,056 --> 00:27:40,149
How long have you been planning this?

366
00:27:40,191 --> 00:27:43,854
Must have taken you forever to find it.

367
00:27:43,895 --> 00:27:46,363
Apparently, I've thought
of nothing else for weeks.

368
00:27:46,397 --> 00:27:47,864
Hurt your grandma's feelings

369
00:27:47,899 --> 00:27:50,390
and a chewed-up wig'll be
the least of your worries.

370
00:27:50,435 --> 00:27:53,632
Hey, Uncle Chuck.
Listen, it's time for cake.

371
00:27:53,671 --> 00:27:56,367
I'll collect the supper plates,
you pass out the forks.

372
00:27:56,407 --> 00:27:58,375
Give you a chance
to say hi to a few folks.

373
00:28:01,713 --> 00:28:04,580
- You remember Cousin Derrick.
- What's with the rat?

374
00:28:04,615 --> 00:28:07,607
Ferret. Harlow.

375
00:28:07,652 --> 00:28:09,085
- Good to be home.
- Yeah.

376
00:28:10,855 --> 00:28:12,322
[Hissing]

377
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:14,951
Got any plates for me?

378
00:28:14,993 --> 00:28:18,053
Do me a favor. Introduce
yourself to Lorelai over there.

379
00:28:18,096 --> 00:28:21,554
She's new and a little shy.

380
00:28:21,599 --> 00:28:24,033
You ain't up to your
matchmaking again, are you?

381
00:28:24,068 --> 00:28:27,401
- Me? Never.
- That's right.

382
00:28:27,438 --> 00:28:30,532
Then I reckon it would be a shame
for anybody to feel left out.

383
00:28:30,575 --> 00:28:34,477
- Uh-huh.
- Excuse me. Got anything for me?

384
00:28:35,747 --> 00:28:38,079
I don't know.
Are you sure you can handle it?

385
00:28:38,116 --> 00:28:39,879
You'd be amazed at what I can handle.

386
00:28:40,651 --> 00:28:42,983
I don't believe we've met.
I'm Robby Ray.

387
00:28:43,021 --> 00:28:44,579
- Oh!
- Ha!

388
00:28:44,622 --> 00:28:45,919
Told you you'd be amazed.

389
00:28:45,957 --> 00:28:47,356
- [Yelping]
- Yahh!

390
00:28:47,392 --> 00:28:51,658
- [Crashing]
- [All gasping]

391
00:28:53,197 --> 00:28:57,827
I got it. It's not that bad,
ladies and gentlemen.

392
00:28:57,869 --> 00:28:59,029
[All exclaiming]

393
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:01,163
Oh, Lord!

394
00:29:02,940 --> 00:29:05,636
[Screaming]

395
00:29:10,848 --> 00:29:13,476
- Howdy!
- [Lorelai] Oh, no.

396
00:29:15,019 --> 00:29:17,112
Oh!

397
00:29:18,689 --> 00:29:20,748
[Grunts]

398
00:29:20,792 --> 00:29:23,727
Whee doggies!
Great news, everybody.

399
00:29:24,629 --> 00:29:26,153
Elvis is alive and well.

400
00:29:29,567 --> 00:29:33,264
[<i># Bless the Broken Road]</i>

401
00:30:18,783 --> 00:30:21,081
I keep thinking
I should change the wallpaper,

402
00:30:21,119 --> 00:30:24,953
but your mom picked this out
when she was about your age.

403
00:30:27,325 --> 00:30:28,952
I like it.

404
00:30:28,993 --> 00:30:31,484
You used to like a lot of things
about coming to see me.

405
00:30:32,997 --> 00:30:35,693
- Grandma...
- It's OK.

406
00:30:35,733 --> 00:30:37,394
I know it's not personal.

407
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:44,566
- I just miss my Miley.
- Why does everyone keep saying that?

408
00:30:44,609 --> 00:30:47,203
Maybe you should be
asking yourself that question.

409
00:30:48,679 --> 00:30:52,240
Caterpillar in a tree
How you wonder who you'll be

410
00:30:54,051 --> 00:30:56,519
Can't go far
But you can always dream

411
00:30:59,524 --> 00:31:02,084
Your daddy used to
say that to you every night.

412
00:31:03,794 --> 00:31:05,523
Not so much anymore.

413
00:31:40,031 --> 00:31:43,831
- [Laughing]
- [Clapping]

414
00:32:13,164 --> 00:32:16,258
[Rooster crowing]

415
00:32:21,939 --> 00:32:25,340
[Travis] Miley! Rise and shine!

416
00:32:25,910 --> 00:32:27,207
[Groans]

417
00:32:35,886 --> 00:32:39,287
Commence Operation
Save Hannah Montana.

418
00:32:39,757 --> 00:32:41,952
Morning! Sleep well?
I've been up for hours.

419
00:32:41,993 --> 00:32:44,461
How about I go feed the chickens
and grab some eggs?

420
00:32:44,495 --> 00:32:48,955
Like I always say, ain't nothin' better
than farm-fresh eggs for breakfast!

421
00:32:51,002 --> 00:32:52,697
Who in the Sam Heck was that?

422
00:32:52,737 --> 00:32:55,137
[<i>#</i> Miley Cyrus: <i>Don't Walk Away]</i>

423
00:33:01,545 --> 00:33:03,274
Here, chick-chick-chick-chick.

424
00:33:03,314 --> 00:33:04,713
[Squawking]

425
00:33:07,318 --> 00:33:09,513
[Shouts] Get away from...

426
00:33:09,553 --> 00:33:11,680
[screams]

427
00:33:11,722 --> 00:33:14,247
Ahh!

428
00:33:16,494 --> 00:33:19,622
How long you think before she
figures out to put down the bucket?

429
00:33:21,365 --> 00:33:23,390
[Groans] Oh, I'm gonna...

430
00:34:08,546 --> 00:34:11,538
All right. Here we go,
one farm-fresh egg.

431
00:34:11,582 --> 00:34:14,073
- Y'all couldn't wait?
- [Robby Ray] Darling, we waited,

432
00:34:14,118 --> 00:34:16,518
but eventually we had to get on
with the rest of our lives.

433
00:34:16,554 --> 00:34:20,183
Get yourself cleaned up, honeybee.
I'm taking you to the farmers' market.

434
00:34:21,058 --> 00:34:22,252
Yay.

435
00:34:23,661 --> 00:34:25,652
[Laughing]

436
00:34:25,696 --> 00:34:28,130
Oh, Robby Ray, my gutters need fixing.

437
00:34:28,165 --> 00:34:31,191
And my truck is making a noise
you just don't want to hear.

438
00:34:31,235 --> 00:34:32,600
I'm on it.

439
00:34:32,636 --> 00:34:34,866
If you need any help,
talk to the foreman.

440
00:34:34,905 --> 00:34:36,896
Might be down by the vegetable patch.

441
00:34:36,941 --> 00:34:38,374
Gotcha.

442
00:34:38,409 --> 00:34:41,435
But don't go squashing my squashes.
They're prizewinners.

443
00:34:45,182 --> 00:34:46,513
Looks like you beat me to it.

444
00:34:50,588 --> 00:34:51,748
Lorelai?

445
00:34:51,789 --> 00:34:55,657
Uh, Ruby didn't... You're the foreman?

446
00:34:55,693 --> 00:34:59,959
- That would be me.
- So that means you're living here, too?

447
00:34:59,997 --> 00:35:02,192
You're good at this.

448
00:35:03,067 --> 00:35:04,466
That's me, right over there.

449
00:35:05,636 --> 00:35:08,332
I was looking for a fresh start,
and I guess Ruby thought

450
00:35:08,372 --> 00:35:12,001
that both me and the farm could
use some looking after, so...

451
00:35:12,042 --> 00:35:14,840
She does like putting things together,
that's for sure.

452
00:35:19,750 --> 00:35:22,241
Lorelai. The foreman.

453
00:35:24,388 --> 00:35:26,618
I'll be dang.

454
00:35:26,657 --> 00:35:28,921
- [Applause]
- [Jackson] All right, you guys.

455
00:35:28,959 --> 00:35:31,427
I'd like to introduce
you all to Tammy Wynette.

456
00:35:31,462 --> 00:35:35,193
She is the fastest two-legged
animal in the world.

457
00:35:35,232 --> 00:35:38,895
She can't fly, she can't swim,
but she sure can...

458
00:35:40,204 --> 00:35:41,899
...bite. Be careful.

459
00:35:41,939 --> 00:35:44,499
- [Squawks]
- [All laughing]

460
00:35:44,542 --> 00:35:47,238
We talked about this.
Unless you want to see ostrich burgers

461
00:35:47,278 --> 00:35:48,768
on the menu at the snack bar...

462
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:51,611
I'll take it from here.
Go feed Miss Pearl.

463
00:35:51,649 --> 00:35:52,980
No, I hate Miss Pearl.

464
00:35:53,017 --> 00:35:57,784
All right, kids.
Who wants to see a real live...

465
00:35:59,123 --> 00:36:02,286
...alligator?
- [All screaming]

466
00:36:02,326 --> 00:36:03,384
[Jackson] Let go!

467
00:36:13,070 --> 00:36:14,799
[Screaming]

468
00:36:18,242 --> 00:36:19,266
Help!

469
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:24,575
- [Chomping]
- Ah!

470
00:36:24,615 --> 00:36:26,913
[Train whistle blowing]

471
00:36:31,222 --> 00:36:33,383
What's with the giant udder?

472
00:36:33,424 --> 00:36:35,858
That is something you
don't see in Beverly Hills.

473
00:36:35,893 --> 00:36:38,487
Old Man Crowley died
