00:54:08,545 --> 00:54:10,570
<i># Throw it all together</i>
<i>That's how we roll #</i>

713
00:54:10,613 --> 00:54:14,982
[cheering]

714
00:54:18,154 --> 00:54:20,122
Our very own Miley Stewart, people.

715
00:54:29,332 --> 00:54:31,357
You got a lot of nerve coming in here.

716
00:54:34,404 --> 00:54:37,202
I'm sorry. I thought this was
a community event.

717
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:40,937
Community. You wouldn't
even know what that word means.

718
00:54:40,977 --> 00:54:44,435
Well, I know that your idea
of it is a thing of the past.

719
00:54:46,182 --> 00:54:48,616
How much y'all raise tonight?

720
00:54:48,651 --> 00:54:50,118
A thousand dollars?

721
00:54:51,120 --> 00:54:53,418
Two thousand dollars?

722
00:54:53,456 --> 00:54:56,118
Whatever it is, I'll double it.

723
00:54:56,159 --> 00:54:57,956
We don't want your money.

724
00:54:57,994 --> 00:54:59,859
At the end of the day
it ain't gonna matter.

725
00:54:59,896 --> 00:55:02,330
You can have a hundred of these,
you ain't gonna raise the money

726
00:55:02,365 --> 00:55:03,855
it's gonna take to save the Meadows,

727
00:55:03,900 --> 00:55:06,528
not unless The Beatles show up
for a benefit concert.

728
00:55:06,569 --> 00:55:10,437
Oh, wait. Small problem. [laughing]

729
00:55:10,473 --> 00:55:12,941
The sooner y'all accept the inevitable,
the sooner we...

730
00:55:12,976 --> 00:55:14,671
Miley knows Hannah Montana.

731
00:55:17,280 --> 00:55:20,511
- Who's that?
- She saved her life surfing.

732
00:55:20,550 --> 00:55:24,850
They're best friends.
She could help us out, right?

733
00:55:24,887 --> 00:55:27,720
Throw a concert.
That would raise a ton of money.

734
00:55:27,757 --> 00:55:30,954
Yeah! Yeah! Do it. Yeah. Call her.

735
00:55:30,994 --> 00:55:33,019
- Yeah.
- Uh...

736
00:55:33,062 --> 00:55:38,022
- I guess I could give her a call.
- [All cheering]

737
00:55:38,067 --> 00:55:41,036
Hannah Montana knows Miley?

738
00:55:41,070 --> 00:55:45,166
[<i>#</i> Hannah Montana: <i>The Best of</i>
<i>Both Worlds: The 2009 Movie Mix]</i>

739
00:55:51,981 --> 00:55:53,778
[Girls screaming]

740
00:55:57,453 --> 00:56:02,481
Oh, my gosh! It's Hannah Montana!
I love you, Hannah!

741
00:56:16,139 --> 00:56:19,540
Oh, my gosh. She's here.
I didn't think she'd actually come.

742
00:56:19,575 --> 00:56:23,636
Thank you! Thank you, thank you,
thank you. Give me a hug. Thank you.

743
00:56:23,680 --> 00:56:26,547
[Camera clicking]

744
00:56:27,517 --> 00:56:29,508
So rustic.

745
00:56:29,552 --> 00:56:31,850
- I love it, Miley.
- Thanks.

746
00:56:31,888 --> 00:56:35,415
This whole "pop star saves hometown"
angle is genius.

747
00:56:35,925 --> 00:56:38,758
Not so genius that I forgive you
for ditching me in New York

748
00:56:38,795 --> 00:56:41,696
and almost costing me my job,
but genius nevertheless.

749
00:56:42,732 --> 00:56:44,063
[Bird cawing]

750
00:56:46,002 --> 00:56:49,028
So you must be Granny.

751
00:56:50,039 --> 00:56:53,634
Adorable. Oh, look at this place.

752
00:56:53,676 --> 00:56:57,112
- It's just so, um... And, uh...
- [cow moos]

753
00:56:57,146 --> 00:57:01,173
- [Sniffs] It always smell like this?
- Pretty much.

754
00:57:02,385 --> 00:57:03,409
Excuse me.

755
00:57:04,420 --> 00:57:07,150
I am so sorry. You are
the best friend I have ever had.

756
00:57:07,190 --> 00:57:09,215
When I thought
you weren't gonna talk to me,

757
00:57:09,258 --> 00:57:12,318
- that I might lose you forever...
- Couldn't lose me if you wanted to.

758
00:57:12,361 --> 00:57:14,090
Good, because I don't want to.

759
00:57:15,164 --> 00:57:18,793
And... sorry about
talking to that reporter guy.

760
00:57:18,835 --> 00:57:23,238
What? Lilly, you're the one that talked
to the reporter? How could you?

761
00:57:23,272 --> 00:57:25,604
I thought this was one of those
"you're sorry, I'm sorry" moments.

762
00:57:25,641 --> 00:57:28,769
It is, and I am. And I swear Hannah'll
never come between us again.

763
00:57:28,811 --> 00:57:29,835
- OK.
- [Knocking]

764
00:57:29,879 --> 00:57:32,347
- Miley?
- Yeah?

765
00:57:32,381 --> 00:57:34,941
[Lorelai] Could I come in
and talk to you and Hannah?

766
00:57:34,984 --> 00:57:36,815
- You be Hannah.
- No, you're Hannah.

767
00:57:36,853 --> 00:57:39,845
- I can't. No, you be Hannah. Stop it.
- [Lorelai] Miley?

768
00:57:39,889 --> 00:57:41,288
It's kind of important.

769
00:57:41,324 --> 00:57:42,348
- No.
- Back.

770
00:57:42,391 --> 00:57:44,154
Stop doing this.

771
00:57:44,193 --> 00:57:46,684
- [Both stammering]
- [Lilly] Stop!

772
00:57:46,729 --> 00:57:49,061
- [Thud]
- [Miley] Come in.

773
00:57:51,234 --> 00:57:53,498
[Gasps]

774
00:57:53,536 --> 00:57:55,197
<i>[Hawaiian music playing]</i>

775
00:57:55,238 --> 00:57:56,865
I'm so sorry. I didn't realize...

776
00:57:56,906 --> 00:57:59,466
No worries. This is just
a little de-stressing.

777
00:57:59,509 --> 00:58:01,136
It helps with Hannah's jet lag.

778
00:58:01,177 --> 00:58:03,839
Jet lag? But California's
only two hours...

779
00:58:03,880 --> 00:58:07,338
Yes. But Hannah only flies west to east,

780
00:58:07,383 --> 00:58:11,217
so... she gains time.
She sometimes has to go

781
00:58:11,254 --> 00:58:14,121
the long way around.
She's actually getting younger.

782
00:58:14,157 --> 00:58:16,955
- Did you want something?
- Uh, yeah. [laughs]

783
00:58:16,993 --> 00:58:18,392
Hi, Hannah.

784
00:58:18,427 --> 00:58:23,455
I'm Lorelai. And we are just
all so grateful that you're here.

785
00:58:23,499 --> 00:58:25,899
Oh, well... [yelps]

786
00:58:26,569 --> 00:58:28,696
Foot massage. [grunts]

787
00:58:28,738 --> 00:58:31,002
- Very L.A.
- [Laughs]

788
00:58:31,040 --> 00:58:33,907
- [Robby Ray] Miley, you up there?
- He doesn't know.

789
00:58:35,344 --> 00:58:38,108
That Hannah's here.
He is going to be so excited.

790
00:58:38,147 --> 00:58:40,513
- Let me tell him.
- I'll take over.

791
00:58:40,550 --> 00:58:44,714
No. Hannah considers me
her personal, you know...

792
00:58:44,754 --> 00:58:46,915
There's these things that... Fine.

793
00:58:48,591 --> 00:58:50,923
Hey, but no talking.

794
00:58:57,233 --> 00:59:00,634
[Lilly] Mmm-hmmm.

795
00:59:00,670 --> 00:59:05,698
So the mayor wants to throw this
big bash in your honor this evening.

796
00:59:05,741 --> 00:59:10,542
And I've had lobsters flown in
and everything just for you.

797
00:59:10,580 --> 00:59:12,445
I hope they don't get too jet-lagged.

798
00:59:14,250 --> 00:59:15,274
Anyway...

799
00:59:16,252 --> 00:59:17,947
Dad!

800
00:59:17,987 --> 00:59:20,922
- Dad, what are you doing?
- Fixing your grandma's gutter.

801
00:59:20,957 --> 00:59:24,017
Hold the ladder for me.
And don't squish the squashes.

802
00:59:24,060 --> 00:59:26,585
Please come down.
It's an emergency. I need you now.

803
00:59:26,629 --> 00:59:29,154
- Is that a yes?
- [Lilly] Mm-hm.

804
00:59:29,198 --> 00:59:33,794
Oh! [laughs]
Oh, that's fantastic. Wow.

805
00:59:33,836 --> 00:59:37,135
What is Lorelai doing
rubbing Hannah's feet?

806
00:59:37,173 --> 00:59:40,074
- Technically, they're Lilly's.
- Stay.

807
00:59:40,109 --> 00:59:43,567
Dad. Dad, we're all set.
I talked to Derrick, and...

808
00:59:43,613 --> 00:59:45,581
- What's with him?
- Shh. Come here.

809
00:59:45,615 --> 00:59:48,277
Hey. Lorelai.

810
00:59:48,317 --> 00:59:51,343
- Why don't you let Hannah rest...
- Shh, I think she's asleep.

811
00:59:53,856 --> 00:59:56,916
Poor thing. Jet lag.

812
00:59:56,959 --> 00:59:59,587
She only flies west to east.

813
00:59:59,629 --> 01:00:03,292
What? That's the stupidest thing
I've ever heard in my life.

814
01:00:03,332 --> 01:00:06,096
Some kind of celebrity thing.

815
01:00:06,135 --> 01:00:09,832
But she said yes.
She's coming to the mayor's dinner.

816
01:00:09,872 --> 01:00:13,433
It was my job to get her there,
and she is coming.

817
01:00:15,544 --> 01:00:17,671
- Great.
- You're going, right?

818
01:00:20,249 --> 01:00:22,217
I don't know.

819
01:00:22,251 --> 01:00:23,582
Is this you asking?

820
01:00:25,388 --> 01:00:28,789
Yeah. I think it might be.

821
01:00:28,824 --> 01:00:30,485
Then this is me accepting.

822
01:00:36,098 --> 01:00:38,692
- I think they're gonna kiss.
- Yes!

823
01:00:38,734 --> 01:00:40,634
Go, Daddy! Go, Daddy!

824
01:00:41,837 --> 01:00:43,065
[Snoring]

825
01:00:44,607 --> 01:00:46,006
- Whoo!
- [Clears throat]

826
01:00:46,042 --> 01:00:49,170
Certainly is getting hot in here.
I think I'll open up the window.

827
01:00:49,211 --> 01:00:52,146
I don't want her
to sleep in a stuffy room.

828
01:00:57,420 --> 01:00:58,978
Daddy, Daddy.

829
01:00:59,989 --> 01:01:02,355
Oh, Jackson!

830
01:01:04,694 --> 01:01:07,857
Are you OK? Watch it. Ladder.

831
01:01:07,897 --> 01:01:09,888
Are you all right?
Let me help you.

832
01:01:09,932 --> 01:01:11,092
I'm OK. I'm OK.

833
01:01:16,005 --> 01:01:18,166
Mmm.

834
01:01:18,207 --> 01:01:21,973
These taste... healthy.
What's in them?

835
01:01:22,812 --> 01:01:23,938
Squash.

836
01:01:26,082 --> 01:01:29,643
Ooh. I want a cowboy.

837
01:01:29,685 --> 01:01:32,313
Sorry. That one's taken.

838
01:01:32,355 --> 01:01:33,549
- Really?
- Yeah.

839
01:01:35,257 --> 01:01:37,248
No.

840
01:01:37,293 --> 01:01:40,421
Maybe. I don't know. It looks like
we're going to be just friends.

841
01:01:41,630 --> 01:01:43,188
But he hasn't met Hannah yet.

842
01:01:44,066 --> 01:01:46,796
- Come on.
- [Drill whirring]

843
01:01:48,437 --> 01:01:50,598
[Drilling]

844
01:01:50,639 --> 01:01:54,598
- So, Ha...
- [drilling loudly]

845
01:01:54,643 --> 01:01:56,076
- Ha...
- [drilling loudly]

846
01:01:57,880 --> 01:01:59,472
Hey, look! It's Hannah Montana!

847
01:02:01,283 --> 01:02:04,616
Oh, hi. Sorry, I... I didn't see you.

848
01:02:04,653 --> 01:02:06,518
I'm Travis. Thanks for coming.

849
01:02:06,555 --> 01:02:11,219
Yeah, happy to help.
This is Lilly. She's my assistant.

850
01:02:11,260 --> 01:02:12,784
Executive assistant.

851
01:02:13,763 --> 01:02:15,754
Welcome to Crowley Corners.

852
01:02:15,798 --> 01:02:19,825
It sure would be nice to have
someone to... show us around.

853
01:02:19,869 --> 01:02:21,393
- Real smooth.
- What?

854
01:02:21,437 --> 01:02:25,931
Look, I really don't think
I'm your guy. But nice to meet you.

855
01:02:25,975 --> 01:02:28,967
- [Sputters]
- No, go. Go!

856
01:02:31,313 --> 01:02:34,908
So... putting up a satellite dish.

857
01:02:35,885 --> 01:02:37,944
It's a birdbath.

858
01:02:37,987 --> 01:02:40,012
- [Laughs]
- I knew that.

859
01:02:41,657 --> 01:02:44,421
Lilly, could you go find
the owner of this fine house

860
01:02:44,460 --> 01:02:46,485
and run them through my dietary needs?

861
01:02:47,163 --> 01:02:48,596
Go. Assist.

862
01:02:49,765 --> 01:02:51,630
OK.

863
01:02:53,702 --> 01:02:56,000
So, you and Miley are pretty close, huh?

864
01:02:56,972 --> 01:02:58,337
You have no idea.

865
01:02:59,975 --> 01:03:03,240
[Laughs] You don't have to answer
if you think this is too personal,

866
01:03:03,279 --> 01:03:06,715
but you think she'd go out
with me if I asked?

867
01:03:06,749 --> 01:03:08,307
You want to go out with Miley?

868
01:03:09,085 --> 01:03:11,747
No, you'd be a real prize.
Don't get me wrong, but...

869
01:03:13,522 --> 01:03:15,922
But Miley...

870
01:03:15,958 --> 01:03:18,051
I can't help but smile
when I'm around her.

871
01:03:19,595 --> 01:03:23,588
I think about her all the time. And I...

872
01:03:23,632 --> 01:03:25,031
You should go ask her out.

873
01:03:26,702 --> 01:03:28,727
- Really?
- Mm-hm.

874
01:03:30,639 --> 01:03:34,040
Yeah. Yeah, I'm going
to do that right now.

875
01:03:34,076 --> 01:03:36,271
No, no. No. Excuse me.

876
01:03:36,312 --> 01:03:39,281
You can't go in there.
She's not home. Miley! She's not home.

877
01:03:39,315 --> 01:03:42,580
She said something about going
to the barn and brushing Blue Jeans.

878
01:03:42,618 --> 01:03:45,678
You should go ask her there.
Go, go, go! Go. Goodbye.

879
01:03:46,489 --> 01:03:47,751
Go!

880
01:03:50,526 --> 01:03:53,154
- Slow down, hot stuff.
- Got to go. Got to go. Got to go.

881
01:03:53,195 --> 01:03:55,322
[Chickens clucking]

882
01:03:55,364 --> 01:03:56,695
Miley?

883
01:03:56,732 --> 01:04:00,395
[Gasping]

884
01:04:01,370 --> 01:04:05,431
[Travis] Miley! Miley, are you?

885
01:04:05,474 --> 01:04:06,839
Hey, slacker.

886
01:04:08,377 --> 01:04:09,844
Uh, hey.

887
01:04:11,247 --> 01:04:13,807
I was just talking
to your friend, Hannah.

888
01:04:15,351 --> 01:04:17,478
Actually, we were talking about you.

889
01:04:17,520 --> 01:04:20,250
Oh, really. Was there
something you wanted to say

890
01:04:20,289 --> 01:04:23,190
or ask me or talk to me about?

891
01:04:24,426 --> 01:04:26,758
Well, I know you're going home soon.

892
01:04:26,795 --> 01:04:29,559
Yeah, I am. That's right,
Travis, keep going.

893
01:04:29,598 --> 01:04:32,931
Um, well...

894
01:04:32,968 --> 01:04:37,337
I was wondering if maybe you would like
to go to dinner with me this evening.

895
01:04:38,407 --> 01:04:40,739
OK. Sure.

896
01:04:40,776 --> 01:04:43,267
I don't think I have
any other plans, so sounds good.

897
01:04:44,280 --> 01:04:46,874
- Cool.
- Cool.

898
01:04:52,655 --> 01:04:53,952
Cool.

899
01:04:53,989 --> 01:04:56,549
Now you're talking.
Oh, that is the one.

900
01:04:56,592 --> 01:04:58,924
Yeah, it would be,
but she's not going.

901
01:04:58,961 --> 01:05:00,258
What do you mean I can't go?

902
01:05:00,296 --> 01:05:02,696
You're the one that promised
Lorelai that Hannah

903
01:05:02,731 --> 01:05:05,928
would be the guest of honor at
the mayor's lobster hoo-hah tonight.

904
01:05:05,968 --> 01:05:08,835
- Actually, Lilly did.
- Actually, Hannah did.

905
01:05:08,871 --> 01:05:10,361
But I promised Travis.

906
01:05:10,406 --> 01:05:13,500
You know what?
Then I'll just leave it up to you.

907
01:05:13,542 --> 01:05:15,305
You do whatever you think is right.

908
01:05:16,378 --> 01:05:17,504
But...

909
01:05:31,660 --> 01:05:34,754
[girls screaming]

910
01:05:38,500 --> 01:05:40,229
It's Hannah Montana!

911
01:05:47,576 --> 01:05:50,272
Can I have your autograph,
Hannah Montana?

912
01:05:56,218 --> 01:05:57,310
[Vita] Smile.

913
01:05:58,487 --> 01:06:00,717
- Yeah!
- Perfect.

914
01:06:03,058 --> 01:06:05,049
Where's Miley?
She should be here by now.

915
01:06:05,094 --> 01:06:09,793
Hon, she's got
East Coast-West Nile disease.

916
01:06:09,832 --> 01:06:12,232
- That sucker's traveling.
- Yeah.

917
01:06:13,435 --> 01:06:16,802
If everybody could please
take their seats.

918
01:06:16,839 --> 01:06:19,967
- Yes, be seated, everybody.
- Find their place card there.

919
01:06:20,009 --> 01:06:25,174
And let me just say that, honestly,

920
01:06:25,214 --> 01:06:27,512
to have someone of your talents,

921
01:06:27,549 --> 01:06:31,383
well, Miss Montana, Hannah, if you will,

922
01:06:31,420 --> 01:06:36,881
your offer of a concert tomorrow to save
Crowley Meadows from such a sad fate,

923
01:06:36,925 --> 01:06:42,192
well, our humble little corner
of the world can't thank you enough.

924
01:06:42,231 --> 01:06:44,699
And if there's ever anything that myself

925
01:06:44,733 --> 01:06:48,032
or the good people of
Crowley Corners can do for you,

926
01:06:48,070 --> 01:06:51,801
anything you need,
all you have to do is...

927
01:06:53,008 --> 01:06:54,532
Where did she go?

928
01:06:55,577 --> 01:07:00,014
Need. I just need to check on my fans.

929
01:07:00,049 --> 01:07:01,914
[Crowd] Hannah, Hannah...

930
01:07:01,950 --> 01:07:07,411
See? But what I really need
is I need to go to the bathroom.

931
01:07:07,456 --> 01:07:10,584
I need to go. Lilly,
come with me. Right now!

932
01:07:14,563 --> 01:07:16,588
Makeup, clothes, it's all in there. Go.

933
01:07:19,868 --> 01:07:23,031
- I'll be right back. Cover for me.
- OK.

934
01:07:31,547 --> 01:07:32,912
[Squeals]

935
01:07:34,383 --> 01:07:35,680
Hey.

936
01:07:35,718 --> 01:07:39,119
- Sorry I'm late.
- You're not late. I was early.

937
01:07:40,122 --> 01:07:43,091
- I got you these.
- Thank you.

938
01:07:45,661 --> 01:07:47,856
You do know you only have one earring?

939
01:07:48,997 --> 01:07:50,362
Trendy L.A. Thing.

940
01:07:54,803 --> 01:07:57,465
- I guess you're going back there soon?
- Mm-hm. Yeah.

941
01:07:57,506 --> 01:07:59,371
Uh...

942
01:08:01,710 --> 01:08:04,008
- I'm going to go ahead and jump.
- Please jump.

943
01:08:06,181 --> 01:08:08,308
- Well, Miley...
- Uh-huh.

944
01:08:08,350 --> 01:08:09,647
Before you leave...

945
01:08:09,685 --> 01:08:13,382
[laughs]... I just...

946
01:08:13,422 --> 01:08:15,822
I really want you to know
how I feel about you.

947
01:08:15,858 --> 01:08:17,382
Mm-hm.

948
01:08:19,128 --> 01:08:24,430
- Um...
- [ringtone sounding]

949
01:08:26,435 --> 01:08:28,062
Is everything all right?

950
01:08:28,103 --> 01:08:32,096
I really should take this. I'm sorry,
it will just be a second. I swear.

951
01:08:32,141 --> 01:08:34,735
I'll probably get better
reception in the back.

952
01:08:34,777 --> 01:08:37,337
I got two bars. Three bars.

953
01:08:38,280 --> 01:08:39,508
Four bars!

954
01:08:40,816 --> 01:08:43,876
[Crowd] Hannah.
Hannah. Hannah. Hannah.

955
01:08:52,761 --> 01:08:53,785
Huh!

956
01:08:55,931 --> 01:08:59,025
Now that our guest of honor
has returned, dig in!

957
01:08:59,067 --> 01:09:00,694
[Laughing]

958
01:09:02,237 --> 01:09:04,000
That's a heck of a crawdaddy, isn't it?

959
01:09:05,307 --> 01:09:06,331
[Grunting]

960
01:09:11,013 --> 01:09:13,208
[Laughing]

961
01:09:14,283 --> 01:09:15,307
Oh!

962
01:09:17,352 --> 01:09:21,186
So, Hannah, you must have
a lot of wonderful stories to tell.

963
01:09:21,223 --> 01:09:22,588
Not really.

964
01:09:24,860 --> 01:09:27,658
I mean there are just so many.

965
01:09:27,696 --> 01:09:30,756
But I don't want this evening
to be all about me.

966
01:09:30,799 --> 01:09:34,132
I mean, everybody's stories
are important, right, Jackson?

967
01:09:34,169 --> 01:09:36,399
- Huh?
- You just started college.

968
01:09:36,438 --> 01:09:39,532
- Tell us about your classes.
- Yeah, my classes. Uh...

969
01:09:39,575 --> 01:09:41,668
- I really like...
- [squeaking]

970
01:09:43,679 --> 01:09:45,340
I think my favorite part is...

971
01:09:47,149 --> 01:09:50,380
Dad, that your little boy
is growing up into a man.

972
01:09:50,419 --> 01:09:51,443
- [Chomping]
- Oh!

973
01:09:54,756 --> 01:09:56,417
Oops, dropped my napkin.

974
01:09:56,458 --> 01:09:57,482
Harlow!

975
01:09:58,527 --> 01:10:00,324
- Harlow!
- Ow!

976
01:10:00,362 --> 01:10:02,455
- What are you doing?
- Looking for a ferret.

977
01:10:02,498 --> 01:10:04,523
- What are you doing?
- Trying to have my first

978
01:10:04,633 --> 01:10:07,033
mature relationship.
Now get back up there.

979
01:10:10,239 --> 01:10:11,263
Found it.

980
01:10:24,353 --> 01:10:25,547
Um...

981
01:10:28,290 --> 01:10:31,987
- I'm having the lobster.
- It's not on the menu.

982
01:10:32,027 --> 01:10:33,289
Right.

983
01:10:41,837 --> 01:10:45,967
Sorry. It's been a weird
couple of days, but...

984
01:10:46,008 --> 01:10:48,203
Yeah.

985
01:10:48,243 --> 01:10:51,644
And I think I know some of
the things you want to tell me.

986
01:10:54,550 --> 01:10:56,609
Yeah?

987
01:10:56,652 --> 01:10:59,644
There are so many things
I want to tell you, too, and...

988
01:11:03,358 --> 01:11:04,985
That's just going to have to wait.

989
01:11:05,027 --> 01:11:07,018
I need to go double-check
on my lobsters.

990
01:11:10,432 --> 01:11:12,593
[Hoedown music plays]

991
01:11:51,540 --> 01:11:52,700
[Mouthing]

992
01:11:52,741 --> 01:11:56,575
- Club soda will take that out.
- Sit! That's enough.

993
01:11:56,612 --> 01:11:58,910
No one is getting up
from this table. No one.

994
01:11:59,715 --> 01:12:01,478
Dessert, anyone?

995
01:12:01,516 --> 01:12:03,882
I'm sure you've all heard
of baked Alaska.

996
01:12:03,919 --> 01:12:06,012
We give you Tennessee flambe.

997
01:12:10,592 --> 01:12:13,493
Mr. Mayor, I assume that
you'd like to say a few final words?

998
01:12:13,528 --> 01:12:15,587
Oh, yes, yes.

999
01:12:15,631 --> 01:12:19,658
Not many people know that the Tennessee
flambe was actually invented by...

1000
01:12:19,701 --> 01:12:22,465
[grunts, laughs]

1001
01:12:22,504 --> 01:12:24,563
[Screaming]

1002
01:12:30,746 --> 01:12:32,179
[Mayor] Come here.

1003
01:12:32,214 --> 01:12:34,239
- Mr. Mayor!
- I got you now.

1004
01:12:34,282 --> 01:12:35,681
[All exclaiming]

1005
01:12:38,620 --> 01:12:39,848
Harlow!

1006
01:12:47,796 --> 01:12:49,093
We got a fire!

1007
01:12:54,136 --> 01:12:55,364
Dang flam it!

1008
01:13:03,545 --> 01:13:05,103
[Both gasping]

1009
01:13:17,092 --> 01:13:20,323
This has all gone very well.
Don't you think?

1010
01:13:25,467 --> 01:13:27,901
Sorry, excuse me. Excuse me.

1011
01:14:24,826 --> 01:14:26,521
Travis, please let me explain.

1012
01:14:27,562 --> 01:14:29,393
Explain what?

1013
01:14:29,431 --> 01:14:32,025
That you've been making fun of me?

1014
01:14:32,067 --> 01:14:35,002
Laughing at me?
Lying to me this whole time?

1015
01:14:36,838 --> 01:14:40,103
I was honest with you.
I told you how I felt.

1016
01:14:40,142 --> 01:14:43,134
- And I feel the same way.
- No, you don't.

1017
01:14:43,178 --> 01:14:45,578
Because I would have never
treated you like that.

1018
01:14:45,614 --> 01:14:49,072
You know what, Miley...
Hannah, whoever you are?

1019
01:14:49,584 --> 01:14:51,108
We're done.

1020
01:14:51,153 --> 01:14:53,451
Travis!

1021
01:14:53,488 --> 01:14:54,853
Travis, please.

1022
01:15:20,482 --> 01:15:23,883
- Did you see?
- Yeah, I saw.

1023
01:15:24,886 --> 01:15:27,855
Robby Ray,
is that you down there? Uh...

1024
01:15:27,889 --> 01:15:31,222
Not now, Lorelai.
I've got some family stuff going on.

1025
01:15:32,093 --> 01:15:35,529
[Lorelai] I'm sorry. It's just
this whole evening was a disaster.

1026
01:15:35,564 --> 01:15:40,365
I just organized the whole thing, and
then that girl comes in and ruins it.

1027
01:15:40,402 --> 01:15:42,393
I don't care if she is here
for a big concert.

1028
01:15:42,437 --> 01:15:45,895
She's got a complicated life.
I know it's hard to understand, but...

1029
01:15:46,908 --> 01:15:48,603
What's going on, Robby Ray?

1030
01:15:50,111 --> 01:15:53,410
I really don't have any time
for secrets and lies.

1031
01:15:53,448 --> 01:15:57,077
I don't know if I could be happy with
somebody comfortable living in them.

1032
01:15:57,118 --> 01:15:59,018
I know. You shouldn't have to be.

1033
01:16:00,422 --> 01:16:02,117
I should have told you the truth.

1034
01:16:03,892 --> 01:16:06,122
The truth is that...

1035
01:16:08,763 --> 01:16:12,426
...I just don't have any place in
my life for a relationship right now.

1036
01:16:12,467 --> 01:16:15,800
There's no room. Miley and me,
we've got to sort through some things.

1037
01:16:15,837 --> 01:16:21,002
And she needs me.
And I kind of need to be there for her.

1038
01:16:23,478 --> 01:16:24,843
I'm sorry.

1039
01:16:26,815 --> 01:16:28,476
Well, me too then.

1040
01:16:30,452 --> 01:16:31,612
Me too.

1041
01:16:36,925 --> 01:16:41,191
[Crowd] Hannah.
Hannah. Hannah. Hannah.

1042
01:16:45,400 --> 01:16:47,595
[Thunder rumbling]

1043
01:17:22,837 --> 01:17:23,997
Hey, caterpillar.

1044
01:17:24,839 --> 01:17:25,999
Thanks.

1045
01:17:26,975 --> 01:17:27,999
No problem.

1046
01:17:37,385 --> 01:17:40,843
- Are you mad?
- No, I'm not mad. You?

1047
01:17:42,824 --> 01:17:43,882
No.

1048
01:17:45,393 --> 01:17:49,796
- How's the song coming?
- I don't know. I'm not sure yet.

1049
01:17:50,899 --> 01:17:52,594
What's it about?

1050
01:17:52,634 --> 01:17:53,794
You.

1051
01:17:55,103 --> 01:17:56,263
Me.

1052
01:17:57,973 --> 01:17:58,997
Us.

1053
01:18:01,309 --> 01:18:02,571
Can I hear it?

1054
01:18:06,548 --> 01:18:11,884
